Description: web directory discovery and reconnaissance scanner
 OpenDoor is a Python CLI scanner for authorized web reconnaissance,
 directory discovery, subdomain enumeration, fingerprint detection, WAF
 detection, controlled header-bypass probing, response filtering, reporting,
 and transport-based scanning workflows.
 .
 It is intended for security researchers, penetration testers, bug bounty
 hunters, DevSecOps engineers, and developers working on authorized exposure
 assessment.
